  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 200°C (400°F).",
    "In a bowl, toss the chickpeas with 1 tbsp olive oil, cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.",
    "Spread the seasoned chickpeas on a baking sheet and roast for 15‑20 minutes, stirring halfway, until golden and crunchy.",
    "While the chickpeas roast, combine the sliced peppadew peppers, red onion, parsley, and mint in a large mixing bowl.",
    "Whisk together the lemon juice, remaining 1 tbsp olive oil, harissa paste, salt, and pepper to make a dressing.",
    "Remove roasted chickpeas from the oven and let cool slightly.",
    "Pour the dressing over the pepper and herb mixture, tossing gently to coat.",
    "Add the roasted chickpeas to the bowl, mix through, and serve immediately."
  ],
